<p>nearly wet through by the time we got on the "Osmanich" she was a very nicely fitted out boat the saloon was as fine as any ever I have seen, in ordinary times she traded between Alexandria &amp; Constantinople. We slept on deck here, &amp; the 2nd Batt. had quarters down below, we had no blankets with us through the fault of our Q.M. &amp; about 10 o'clock that night our Dr (Dr Thompson) came round it was a bitterly cold night &amp; drizzling rain was falling making everything miserable, he pulled up opposite me &amp; asked me the reason why we had no blankets &amp; I told him pretty quick the cause of it, did'nt he perform</p>
